Topic: SRT (Situation Reaction Test) 🧠⚡

👉 This is the most practical test in SSB
👉 It checks: “What will you DO in real life?”

1️⃣ What is SRT?

You will be given:

60 situations
⏱️ ~30 minutes total

👉 You must write your reaction quickly

⚡ Reality of SRT
Very less time
No thinking deeply
Your natural reaction = your personality
2️⃣ What SSB Checks

They observe:

Decision making
Responsibility
Courage
Presence of mind
Leadership

👉 Not perfect English ❌
👉 Only your actions ✅

3️⃣ How to Answer (MOST IMPORTANT)
❌ Wrong Way

“ I will think what to do ”

👉 No action ❌

✅ Correct Way

“ He informs authorities and helps injured person reach hospital ”

👉 Action + responsibility ✅

🧠 Golden Rule

👉 Situation → Immediate Action → Positive Outcome

4️⃣ Types of Situations
🔹 1. Daily Life Problems

👉 Friend failed, exam stress

🔹 2. Emergency Situations

👉 Accident, fire

🔹 3. Social Situations

👉 Helping others, teamwork

🔹 4. Personal Problems

👉 Failure, weakness

5️⃣ Example Questions
Q1

You see a man injured on road.

✅ Answer:
“He provides first aid and takes him to nearest hospital.”

Q2

You failed in exam.

✅ Answer:
“He analyses mistakes and prepares better for next attempt.”

Q3

Your friend is cheating.

✅ Answer:
“He advises friend to be honest and informs teacher if needed.”

6️⃣ Common Mistakes

❌ No action
❌ Unrealistic answers
❌ Negative thinking
❌ Too long sentences
❌ Ignoring responsibility

7️⃣ PRO STRATEGY (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 Always show:

Quick action
Responsibility
Helping nature
Logical thinking

👉 Avoid:

Violence
Escaping situation
Blaming others
8️⃣ Practice Set (DO NOW)

Write quick responses:

1️⃣ You are late for exam
2️⃣ Your teammate is not cooperating
3️⃣ You see fire in building
4️⃣ You lost your important document
5️⃣ Your junior is depressed

⏱️ Time: 30 sec each

🧠 SECRET TIP

👉 SRT answers must match your:

TAT stories
WAT sentences

💥 Consistency = Selection

📊 Quick Summary
Factor	Focus
Situations	60
Time	30 min
Style	Action-based
Goal	Show OLQs
